cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.GT, cs.MM, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with secure communication and information theory, which suggests that cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category. The presence of an active adversary and the need for secure communication also suggest that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a likely category. The use of game-theoretic framework suggests that cs.GT (Game Theory) is also a possible category. The mention of broadcasting and sharing of secret keys suggests that cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing) are also possible categories.
